  "body_text": "Montana (Mont.)\n(p.297)\nhttp://montanacourts.org/\nhttps://archive.legmt.gov/statute/\nPublic domain citation format:\nMontana has adopted a public domain citation format for cases after January 1, 1998. The format is:\nMont. Env’t Info. Ctr. v. Dep’t of Env’t Quality, 1999 MT 248, 296 Mont. 207, 988 P.2d 1236.\nMont. Env’t Info. Ctr. v. Dep’t of Env’t Quality, 1999 MT 248, ¶ 21, 296 Mont. 207, 988 P.2d 1236.\nFor additional instruction, consult Order\nIn re\n: Opinion Forms and Citation Standards of the Supreme Court of Montana, and the Adoption of Public Domain and Neutral-Format Citation (Dec. 16, 1997), and Order in the Matter of Amending Citations Standards for the Montana Supreme Court (Jan. 22, 2009).\nSupreme Court\n(\nMont.\n): Cite to\nP.\n,\nP.2d\n, or\nP.3d\n, if therein.\nPacific Reporter\n1883–date\nP., P.2d, P.3d\nMontana Reports\n1868–date\nMont.\nState Reporter\n1945–date\nState Rptr.\nStatutory compilations:\nCite to\nMont. Code Ann.\n, if therein.\nMontana Code Annotated\nMont. Code Ann.\n§ x-x-x (\n<year>\n)\nWest's Montana Code Annotated\nMont. Code Ann.\n§ x-x-x (West\n<year>\n)\nSession laws\nLaws of Montana\n<year>\nMont. Laws\n<page no.>\nAdministrative compilation\nAdministrative Rules of Montana\nMont. Admin. R.\n<rule no.>\n(\n<year>\n)\nAdministrative register\nMontana Administrative Register\n<iss. no.>\nMont. Admin. Reg.\n<page no.>\n(\n<month day, year>\n)",
